Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at Merit Medical Systems in South Jordan, Utah, highlighting the success of the American economy under President Trump and urging support for the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA). Pence praised the growth of the economy, including the creation of 6.2 million new jobs and the lowest unemployment rate in 50 years. He emphasized the importance of passing the USMCA and called on Congress to take action. Pence also recognized the accomplishments of Merit Medical and its employees, highlighting their contributions to the economy and the company's success. He concluded his speech by expressing his faith and confidence in the American people and the future of the nation.